##Q & A on the life and death of a Wuhan girl

Wechat, bingdianweekly

Features, China Youth Daily's in depth reporting brand. We believe that news has more than one day of life.

Art Editor, Chaohusaurus

This article is about 8490 words long

Estimated reading time: 22 minutes

Author | Zhongqingbao Zhongqing.com reporter, Wang Mengying

Editor | Jin jin-ja

Dong wanting, a 22 year old from Wuhan, had written a suicide note by hand. Unable to walk at the time, the new coronavirus-infected man slept for a day, then fumbled for a pen and paper and felt himself face the face of death, weeping in fear.

On January 20,2020, she started coughing and running a fever. CT SCAN of the lungs shows a ground-glass opacity. She visited three hospitals nine times, was isolated at home for a week and a half, was isolated for 11 days, had four nucleic acid tests, was hospitalized as a critical patient for 19 days, swallowed 20 pills a day, and had 11 tubes of blood drawn. Her city also declared "war, " and more than 40,000 health care professionals from across the country joined the fight.

March 10, Dong wanting to check the results of discharge standards, transferred to the isolation point, nucleic acid test does not "Fu Yang" can be recovered home. In this struggle for survival, a young senior finds many answers.

1

The shadow of death, initially expressed as uncertainty, creeps into life. Dong wanting is not clear from when, in the mind of doubt bigger and bigger, hold full frowziness chest cavity: Am I also infected?

Her Gengzi year began with a high fever, when she opened her eyes just past zero and took her temperature, 38.8 degrees Celsius.

When she has a fever, she feels heavy and the pain sharp. She was tired, but couldn't sleep for several nights, and her musculoskeletal muscles ached, especially her lower back. The sensation of organ failure is so intense that it's hard to describe it to a healthy person -- as if she could feel the Alveoli on one side of her lungs don't seem to stretch on the other. High fever for a few days, latent for a few days, and even stronger ground to attack. Diarrhea on the way.

People in Wuhan turn the pages of their calendars to the Spring Festival, and the number of confirmed cases of new pneumonia is increasing. Dong wanting to have heard passers-by talk about "panic" , dumpling restaurant in the local elderly to wear a mask to argue. Many people in the supermarket, I do not know is for the new year, or because of the "closed" hoarding goods. Festive song, mixed with a male voice broadcast:"... remind you to wash your hands frequently..."

When she got off the elevator, she met the courier, who didn't have a mask. She sent one, for fear of infecting a hard-working man.

She is a drop in the tide of consulting. On January 23, she went to Wuhan Tongji Hospital, arrived at 9 am, got more than 900, was told that 4 pm is possible to see a doctor. Then she went to the Puai Hospital, where she moved for three hours as the line dragged on and waited for blood to be drawn. She didn't get a drip -- the drip was going to the ER, and the ER was full.

On the first day of the New Year, she got up early and went to Tongji Hospital. Not a lot of patients. She finally got a chest Ct. . Got The results this afternoon: ground-glass shadow on both lungs. She didn't cry, she didn't even have a look on her face, her hands were shaking.

Within four hours of waiting for the result, she went home for dinner and watched the TV drama "Qingyunian" for a while. The hero seems to have solved another big problem. She plays the show on a loop, and the tablet is plugged in 24 hours a day. Even if you're doing something else, you need the voice of the character to fill in the background.

Tongji Hospital gave her three shots, but she didn't get the third. On January 25, she was banned from driving in central Wuhan.

While she was in the hospital getting fluids, she silently watched the people around her and wrote it down in her diary when she got home. She witnessed a parting: The woman with her five or six year old son on one side and the man on the other. The man called out, "Son! " The little boy was in a daze, but the woman moved her lips and did not come near.

Another couple: "experts say albumin injections may work. " "Why, it's going to cost a fortune. " "It's going to save your life, too. "

"My whole house is infected, " she heard an old man say. "In the house. I'm isolated in Hanyang, my son is in the Hankou Hospital, my daughter-in-law is in Wuchang, and neither of us are together. "

She heard a young girl on the phone and guessed that it might be her family on the other end. The girl said: "YOU DO NOT COME OVER! I want a person quarantine! I stay in a hotel, go anywhere, I do not go to you there... This is an infectious disease, people will die! You do not have to be infected to stop, I do not come back! "

The girl hung up and cried again. The phone's still vibrating. They're calling back. Tung yuen-ting Also began to cry.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Dong wanting to write her isolation diary on the surface of the capsule. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Fourth Wuhan Hospital. She's been there three times. For the first time, the hospital was unable to receive treatment and was undergoing urgent rehabilitation to accommodate the new pneumonia admission requirements. The second time, she saw eight doctors, four consultation rooms and a triage table at the fever clinic. With the triage table as the center, the patient surrounded by several layers, each layer would like to be closer to the center step. "people in Wuhan usually don't have the habit of waiting in line, let alone in special times. " The third time was on January 26, and the hospital has been restored to basic order. A nurse advised her: There is no diagnostic kit, there is no point in waiting in line, go home and Quarantine.

A few months ago, Ms. Dong's expectations for the year were graduation projects and graduate applications. What she didn't know at the time was that a new coronavirus the size of one sesame seed per 100,000 was floating around.

It was a long time before she felt connected to the fate of the city that had given birth to her. On January 23, the day after her fever began, Wuhan was "sealed off" . She was admitted to the hospital on 17 February as a critically ill patient in isolation following the rapid increase in the number of confirmed cases in Wuhan. Her condition has improved since March. New Cases in Wuhan Drop to double digits for first time.

On Feb. 8, more than two weeks after Dong began showing symptoms, 33,728 new cases of pneumonia were confirmed in mainland China, exceeding the final figure for the SARS period, Zhong Nanshan said on a television program. Wuhan Raytheon Mountain Hospital also began to use, the same day delivery of 1600 beds. That day, she received a call informing her of the transfer.

It was late afternoon when we arrived at the quarantine point in the Qiaokou District district, where the dormitories of Wuhan's First Vocational Education Centre had been requisitioned.

From the first floor lobby, she could see a full moon. Up and down the stairs a few times, the day is getting thicker and thicker, and "the moon has been there" , large, golden, very good-looking. She remembered that it was the Lantern Festival and the Spring Festival was over.

She remembers that on New Year's Eve, she was so desperate to see the gala that she hadn't seen it in years.

In her tiny rented room alone, she lay down without dinner and watched CCTV New Year's Gala live on her tablet. The opening is the song and dance "Ode to the Spring Tide" . Color splashed on the screen, the stars Sing "the first month to the first month is the first month, gongs and drums suona firecrackers sound. ". Since 2013, Wuhan has reintroduced a ban on fireworks and firecrackers, and the night outside the window is silent. After about two shows, she fell asleep.

2

On the first day at the isolation point, the staff showed her to the storage room on the first floor to collect bedding and other materials. This quarantine was only opened the first day, and she belongs to the second group of residents. She started at the bottom, because the closer she got to the first floor, the easier it was to save. The other patients were apparently of the same mind, and she went all the way to the fifth floor to find the empty room.

It was very quiet, and she occasionally heard a cough in the corridor, "almost out of breath, " from one of the tenants.

If you don't take into account the virus in your system, it's like being a freshman. She ran up and down, took things back to her room, made the bed and boiled water. The room is square with a small balcony, the sheets are folded new blue plaid cloth.

When the quilt was finished, I had to ask for a mattress cover. Wearing a sweater and down jacket, Dong wrapt in the mattress, a night to wake up. She felt that this winter in Wuhan is particularly cold, "may also be psychological reasons. ".

The fever clinic was set up in a small, isolated room on a vacant lot, with a long line of people waiting outside. It was a windy day and she wore seven layers inside and out, wearing a scarf, hat and gloves. For the first time, she realized that the height of cold was that it was no longer cold.

For the safety of the patient, the door of the isolation point is not allowed to close, and a towel is wrapped around the latch of the door to prevent automatic tape. "It was like a symphony, " she said one day as she watched the warm yellow turning to blue white and the heavy snow falling.

From the first cough to the quarantine, she never told her mother. The sick daughter felt the need to protect her mother. Public transportation stopped, and mom didn't have a car to actually help. She felt that telling her mother would only make her feel powerless and worried for nothing.

The outbreak pushed her and dad together. She found herself given the opportunity to renew her father-daughter relationship. She made no secret that she came from an "incomplete family" . Her parents divorced when she was young. The father remarried and had another daughter. Her mother worked hard and she was almost brought up by her grandmother.

In Dong wanting to see, the concern of the father always takes a kind of not from cent to say of dogmatism. And she's used to making her own decisions. She followed her passion and entered art high school and then Art College. My father always disapproved of the decision and found it difficult to find a job. "You don't have the talent, " he persuades, unaware that the phrase cuts like a knife.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Tung yuen-ting paints a wall painting in a hospital

Before this winter, father and daughter only meet in the festival. The grown-up daughter and the middle-aged father no longer have a conflict, they maintain a polite distance. This time, Tung told her father about her condition. The latter has a private car, can take her to and from the hospital, the car window is more and more open in Wuhan.

For a time, she didn't want to wait in line at the hospital. She felt useless and her body was becoming more and more exhausted. Her father was against it, and always made her come again. He wanted to save his daughter, in the dogmatic way he was used to. The two of them often argued about it.

One of the conflicts broke out during a phone call between the two men. Halfway through the fight, the girl heard and her father cried.

For the first time in her life, Dong wanting experienced her father's tears. She found that her father could choke up and continue to speak his mind almost without interruption. At this moment, two people abundant emotions let her "shock" and "pain" . She realized, my God, Dad loves me.

3

She saw in the news outside the situation, "Jianghan road no one" , this is she hit the record has never seen the scene. She had never seen a hotter city than Wuhan.

In late winter and early spring of 2019, she was walking the streets of the city with a school camera. This is the practical part of the art course reading the city.

The building is busy. Wuhan, a trading port added to the Treaty of Tientsin, is now the fourth largest port in the country in terms of foreign trade volume, and the "thoroughfare of nine provinces. ". Different architectural styles jostle here, and she takes pictures to compare them in her books, recognizing Guangdong, Zhejiang and European styles.

Modern high-rises cluster around the low red roofs of "Rifen" . Rifen was the concession of Wuhan during the semi-colonial period, and is now a village within the city. "Bihu is connected, and Leili is the dwelling place of the house" and "Li" is the dwelling place of the House. Dong's grandmother used to live in Jixianli, which has since been demolished. In 2019, she subleased a studio in San Francisco, where she observed from morning to night. She found residents mostly elderly and manual workers, many sanitation workers, with fluorescent strips of orange-red vests in the lane disappeared. Residential floor cable pull very low, drying of the various colors of shirts and trousers fluttering. The yellow cat was lying between the shadows and the sunlight, squinting.

The people of Wuhan, "always want to be vigorous and vigorous in word of mouth" . Wuhan dialect, with its striking cadences, is always "very aggressive" and "Hankou dialect is particularly aggressive" . Jianghan road is a pedestrian street, crowded, signs Neon, loudspeakers playing pop music, "It seems that there will always be a quarrel" : customers for the price, pedestrians and shop quarrel.

Dong wanting to live in the separation is also heard the most quarrel, parents, wife and children, family short story. Passersby strolled by, not feeling much excitement. After the argument, the smell of food wafted up again.

In her eyes, Wuhan is full of "The flavor of rivers and lakes" , "smoke and fire" is directly reflected in the residential buildings on the external walls.

After the 2019 Military Games, the city's appearance has been greatly improved. Before this, Dong wanting to climb the street with lampblack mark commonly and cement metope. Lampblack comes from the heavy taste kitchen that is in full swing, Wuhan Person Is"good 7 lo"(person that loves to eat) .

"good seven guys" Dong wanting "mouth Diao" , "by Wuhan coddled" . She would go all the way to Laotongcheng to eat fried bean skin and to the north Rd. to buy and sell it. The kitchen knife "Dong" ground chops down the duck neck, the hot dry surface "pricks" one sound inhales the oral cavity. "Too early" (at breakfast) she usually does not wear make-up, or she will spend it all. The flies, the plastic tables and chairs, the hot air, the Hankou soup powder. She sipped and "sweated to an incredible degree" . Pepper put enough, can the tears of outsiders down.

Dong wanting to feel oneself is not like Wuhan person all the time, "the speech is not like, do not have imposing manner" . She considered herself "the quintessential art student, " introverted, sensitive and constantly worried that she could not speak as clearly as she could write. Growing up with only a few close friends, she was somewhat apprehensive about being exposed to an unfamiliar world.

She had been depressed for a time in this hot city. In addition to anxiety about the progress of art studies, young souls often get bogged down in grand questions. She read Albert Camus's the stranger, in which he says, "I have lived this way, and I may live another way, " and all life inevitably leads to death. She looked at her "ordinary, ordinary" life and asked herself: What is the meaning of life?

A 22-year-old girl doesn't have the answers.

"Is it love? I don't know, " she said. Even when she was writing her suicide note, she couldn't write a word of love.

The night of the fever she thought of her grandmother. Wuhan called her grandmother "Home" , she looked up information when turning to a Hubei Children's Song: Shake Hands, go home, do not kill chickens, play wine. Take foreign ships, under the Hankou, eat eggs, drink rice wine, buy on CIBA to turn away... a Home Cooked Bacon, 100 incense enough.

Her family, as the children's song goes, always have endless good food, to give the little grandson. Dong's childhood in her grandmother's Old House spent junior high school, she and her grandmother live in a cousin's home, often sleeping together at night in the Cousin Living Room Sofa.

The Old Lady in the Third Day of Tung Yuen Ting found terminal cancer, survived a major operation. Her family didn't lie to her, and she didn't seem to care about dying. The operation was over, the anesthetic still in effect, and the man with his eyes closed mumbled, as if he had been playing Mah Jongg in a dream.

Ms Dong plans to show her feelings for her grandmother in her graduation project, which she has never said. We haven't started yet. She's trapped in her house with the virus. She didn't know if she would have a chance to graduate, or even if she would survive, but at some point it became clear to her that she was going to "make use of everything that was at hand" to come up with a graduation project.

At any moment of strength, she began to make paper. DISSOLVE PAPER NAPKINS in water to make pulp, then shape a little bit, knead to form the shape of a grandma's dress on hand.

It was a brown doublet that had been worn for many years. The oil stains give the fabric a sculptural feel. The oil comes from the ordinary meals of countless dead days.

4

She didn't know whether she was doing it to distract herself from death, or to prepare for the possibility that she might die and leave something behind. Maybe it's both.

Before the outbreak, she thought about death countless times, philosophically or artistically. But this time, she heard the voice in her head, simple and strong: I want to live. That "ordinary, ordinary" life, she did not want to give up.

At one point, this desire manifested itself in anger. When the sun occasionally came out, the little patient sat on the balcony of the isolation point, wrapped in the only down jacket he had brought, holding Lu Xun's the scream. At night, she reread North Island's answer: to read the condemned voices before the trial: I tell you, the world, I Florida -- I do not Florida -- believe it!

When we moved her to quarantine, we didn't give her much time to pack. She loves to travel, "just go" , always have a toiletry bag and a simple change of clothes, saving time for picking out books. She had bought a copy of the big question, a book on the basics of Philosophy, in her freshman year, when she settled down to read it. She tried to answer the question posed in the book: If she had a few minutes left to live, she wanted to call someone she didn't know.

Meanwhile, more and more people are barging into this introverted girl's time line of Silence.

School counsellors, including Ms Tung's, relay daily messages for help in various groups. Students joined the relay, the information spread out, no one knows which of the dissemination of which node can ultimately help. More and more numbers came into contact with her cell phone, both from classmates and strangers. People want to know how she's doing, and they're trying to help.

During home isolation, the fever of Dong wanting to participate in a graduation project of the online report. Her Mentor expressed dissatisfaction with her progress, which made her very upset. The teacher has always been strict, in her eyes almost "harsh. ".

Tung feared and respected him. He was a teacher in the reading city course. Under his guidance, the born and bred Wuhan girl rediscovered her accustomed city, the color was bright in her eyes. Also at his suggestion, she experimented with Napkin Art.

Dong wanting to tell a tutor, oneself wrote a suicide note. On the other end of the line, the teacher, who was in his late 20s, was silent for a long time, telling his students, you can think about this in 60 years.

Later, Dong wanting to hear that the teacher went to the school, asked to save his students.

At the isolation point of Qiaokou District's First Vocational Education Center, Tung met the rescue team leader Ma Yufei, who greeted her in the lobby, and the person in charge of the isolation point. She remembered captain ma saying to her, "If you have something, you must tell me. "

Ma Yufei was a volunteer, born in Jingzhou, Hubei, working in Wuhan, with an accent halfway between the two. Had it not been for the outbreak, the 45-year-old would have been in the UK celebrating Chinese New Year, reunited with his wife and son, who live there. He's contracted before, worked with the government, heard about the quarantine from them. After the ticket was canceled, he thought, let's do something about it, so he came here.

When it opened on February 7th, more than 300 people moved in. Cars from all the neighborhoods usually arrive at 3:00 a.m. late. According to Mahut Fei, this period of almost all patients are suspected, "nucleic acid test a positive" , the average stay of 3 days will be transferred to the hospital.

The patients had a two-tiered age range, with the oldest over 70 and the youngest 17. There were 13 families living in the quarantine, all of them infected, in small, inaccessible cells.

Ma Yufei led more than 70 volunteers from morning to night, a trip on the ward to put food, temperature. Tired, just lying in the office of the fold-up bed. The quarantine site has a wechat group where patients contact volunteers. However, most elderly patients will not use smartphones, to toothbrush, hot water, can only wait for volunteers to ask. Most of the elderly have underlying illnesses and rely on volunteers to buy medicines. There was only one pharmacy in Qiaokou District, which was open a few hours a day.

The whole building is struggling against the shadow of an unknown fate. Eight out of 13 families have had conflicts that required volunteers to break up. Ma and his colleagues also need to pay special attention to the mental health of elderly patients. Some of them have shown suicidal tendencies and "hit the wall" , but were saved in time.

There are two doctors in the quarantine every day. Doctors come from a variety of sources, some from provincial medical teams, some from local volunteer doctors.

Ms Dong was subjected to four nucleic acid tests. Every time she waited for the result, she had a small, almost naive expectation that there might be some mistake. Four Times, three times negative. Later news mentioned that many patients with new coronary pneumonia false negative reagent box situation, to determine with the imaging results.

Her lungs are drowning. Help information shows that she was "obvious chest pain, swollen lymph swallowing difficulties, high fever cough, shortness of breath. ". Onset 1 month, home isolation for a week and a half, isolation point isolation for 9 days, reported 3 physical discomfort, to the hospital treatment of the opportunity has not come. On the night of February 11th, she wrote a suicide note.

On the morning of February 17, Ma Yufei went to Dong wanting's room and brought her a box of tissues. Ms Dong always thought this was a lucky turn. In fact, Mahut had been following her for three days. The volunteer told him that the girl in the room had stopped eating breakfast, and he thought something was wrong.

Ma yu-fei inquired about the specific situation, for Dong wanting to find a doctor. The doctor judged it to be a serious case. Dong wanting to know outside the situation, ma yu-fei is very clear bed tension, serious outside there are more serious. He told the China Youth Daily's China Youth Daily Online reporter that he used a bit of personal connections. Dong wanting to hear, he runs to prevent epidemic headquarters"quarrel".

That evening, Tung yuen-ting received the news, overnight transfer to Hanyang District, Wuhan Tongji Hospital for treatment. Until she left, she didn't know what captain horse looked like -- a protective suit covering his face.

Ma Yu Fei was unable to forget Dong wanting to see to his eyes, "that kind of helpless. ". This girl reminds him of his son.

5

In Tongji, Hanyang, sound and light are back. Even in the middle of the night, the lights in the hospital don't go out completely. She could hear doctors and nurses in Hazmat suits walking up and down the hallway, a sort of plastic bag-waving, heavy-footed sound. But it reassured her.

When she arrived at the hospital, she called her mother to tell her that she had been admitted to the hospital with a new case of pneumonia. Her mother told her to get well and not sound surprised. Dong wanting to feel suddenly, the mother may guess very early the daughter's situation is not right, the mother knows.

During the first few days in hospital, she slept almost day and night. Side effects of the medication include vomiting and nausea. Slowly, her sobriety grew longer and longer. Doctors told her that in her body, the young immune system was battling the virus with the help of drugs.

She began to discover that she was "a Wuhan native after all" . The people of Wuhan are obsessed, and she's so obsessed with living.

Everything surprised her: The Sky outside the window, the shadows on the wall, the beautiful color of the sulfuric acid paper that covered the apples through the light. This is the second time she's been surprised. In the study of "reading city" , she read a regret: "common people living in one place for decades, read all the vicissitudes of life but turn a blind eye to become a long-lived visitors, in the end there is no master mood

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On a pear, Tung noted the date on which she had been quarantined. Photo courtesy of the respondents

Round and round the stem of the pear she wrote the date, every day from the onset of the disease to the present day. She swallowed more than 20 pills a day, pulled out a board of capsules, wrote down her isolation diary on the surface, and carefully tucked it back in. And a pill on which she drew a little bat.

The night she left the quarantine to go to the hospital, her mentor told her: Everyone does what they can, and the world will be better and better.

She repeated the words. The hospital was recruiting volunteers to assist nurses among its patients, and she hesitated for a whole day before signing up. The other person is happy: You are the first.

It's something she's never done before. Before she got sick, it took her two years to do her psych work and attend class meetings. She's still introverted and nervous about connecting with people, but she's starting to feel that she needs that connection and appreciates it.

Nurses have a heavy workload, not just medical, but also responsible for carrying materials, put food for patients and other chores. Protective clothing enveloped the whole body, Dong wanting at first can not distinguish who is who, can only hear their exhaustion from the voice. She later discovered that the suits didn't cover her eyes, and that everyone's eyes were different.

The volunteers, most of whom were young, tried to help the nurses when they were in good health, helping to ease the burden of their chores. On Women's Day, Dong wanting received a letter signed "all medical workers in A10 ward" , written on big red paper, wishing "the little beauty of our department a speedy recovery. ". Along with it was a rose and a box of chocolates.

They produced an audio program that was broadcast over the hospital's broadcast system. Tung yuen-ting is in charge of organizing staff. In the first programme, a young man said: There is no great matter except life and death.

Spring has arrived in Wuhan as promised. Ma felt the temperature rise, when busy shirt jacket is enough. At his isolation point, the number of suspected cases has been greatly reduced, and the occupants are generally not in too bad a condition. The task was reduced to 26 volunteers. He would occasionally think of flying out of Wuhan after the epidemic was over, in time for a late reunion with his wife and children.

Senior Student Tung yuen-ting worries about her graduation every day. She plans to study abroad, but IELTS's exams have been postponed, and the portfolio she needs to apply to school has yet to be sorted out. In the ward, to report to the instructor the progress of the graduation project time again, she began to nervous from the night before. The girl tentatively said that her thesis is not easy to write, the instructor returned four words: According to the requirements to write.

When she left the hospital, she was still wearing the same pink down jacket she hadn't changed in 50 days. Her bed in Ward A10 was empty, and on the ward wall was a picture of her and her fellow volunteers: a rabbit wearing a mask. Before that, the hospital had undergone an emergency renovation and the walls had been whitewashed. She wrote a "discharge letter" to the doctors and nurses, because of prudence, wrote three times, "those unimaginable difficulties, except you, who knows... this sick Wuhan, because of you, just have the antidote. "

She went on to write: "DON'T BE NUMB! ... Truth, which none of us can escape, is the only answer. "

She will always think of her grandmother, her "home. ". After her grandmother's operation, she was worried about the old man's health. But year after year, the old woman persevered, taking care of her grandchildren and preparing three meals a day. "Big Heart" , "a typical Wuhan People" .

It's a little different. Every year before the Spring Festival, families in Wuhan to pickled fish sausage sausage sausage sausage. It's manual labor, and Grandma's specialty. After the operation, the old man never did it again.

Dong wanting to feel this epidemic changed oneself forever, she"became braver". For the moment, she had an answer to the big question that had plagued her. Maybe she got the order wrong: "I was always looking for meaning in life, because I thought, life has to have meaning before it has power. Now I think life itself is power. "

Wuhan will be "the most important city in her life" , and she is looking forward to leaving one day to see the bigger world -- a dream she wrote in her suicide note at the age of 22.
